{"nodes":[{"content":"About App-V 5.0 Dynamic Configuration","pos":[11,48]},{"content":"About App-V 5.0 Dynamic Configuration","pos":[62,99]},{"content":"About App-V 5.0 Dynamic Configuration","pos":[274,311]},{"content":"You can use the dynamic configuration to customize an App-V 5.0 package for a user.","pos":[314,397]},{"content":"Use the following information to create or edit an existing dynamic configuration file.","pos":[398,485]},{"content":"When you edit the dynamic configuration file it customizes how an App-V 5.0 package will run for a user or group.","pos":[487,600]},{"content":"This helps to provide a more convenient method for package customization by removing the need to re-sequence packages using the desired settings, and provides a way to keep package content and custom settings independent.","pos":[601,822]},{"content":"Advanced: Dynamic Configuration","pos":[827,858]},{"content":"Virtual application packages contain a manifest that provides all the core information for the package.","pos":[861,964]},{"content":"This information includes the defaults for the package settings and determines settings in the most basic form (with no additional customization).","pos":[965,1111]},{"content":"If you want to adjust these defaults for a particular user or group, you can create and edit the following files:","pos":[1112,1225]},{"content":"User Configuration file","pos":[1231,1254]},{"content":"Deployment configuration file","pos":[1260,1289]},{"content":"The previous .xml files specify package settings and allow for packages to be customized without directly affecting the packages.","pos":[1291,1420]},{"content":"When a package is created, the sequencer automatically generates default deployment and user configuration .xml files using the package manifest data.","pos":[1421,1571]},{"content":"Therefore, these automatically generated configuration files simply reflect the default settings that the package innately as from how things were configured during sequencing.","pos":[1572,1748]},{"content":"If you apply these configuration files to a package in the form generated by the sequencer, the packages will have the same default settings that came from their manifest.","pos":[1749,1920]},{"content":"This provides you with a package-specific template to get started if any of the defaults must be changed.","pos":[1921,2026]},{"content":"Note","pos":[2030,2034]},{"content":"The following information can only be used to modify sequencer generated configuration files to customize packages to meet specific user or group requirements.","pos":[2039,2198]},{"content":"Dynamic Configuration file contents","pos":[2207,2242]},{"content":"All of the additions, deletions, and updates in the configuration files need to be made in relation to the default values specified by the package's manifest information.","pos":[2244,2414]},{"content":"Review the following table:","pos":[2415,2442]},{"content":"User Configuration .xml file","pos":[2541,2569]},{"content":"Deployment Configuration .xml file","pos":[2623,2657]},{"content":"Package Manifest","pos":[2710,2726]},{"content":"The previous table represents how the files will be read.","pos":[2764,2821]},{"content":"The first entry represents what will be read last, therefore, its content takes precedence.","pos":[2822,2913]},{"content":"Therefore, all packages inherently contain and provide default settings from the package manifest.","pos":[2914,3012]},{"content":"If a deployment configuration .xml file with customized settings is applied, it will override the package manifest defaults.","pos":[3013,3137]},{"content":"If a user configuration .xml file with customized settings is applied prior to that, it will override both the deployment configuration and the package manifest defaults.","pos":[3138,3308]},{"content":"The following list displays more information about the two file types:","pos":[3310,3380]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>User Configuration File (UserConfig)<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> – Allows you to specify or modify custom settings for a package.","pos":[3386,3491]},{"content":"These settings will be applied for a specific user when the package is deployed to a computer running the App-V 5.0 client.","pos":[3492,3615]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Deployment Configuration File (DeploymentConfig)<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> – Allows you to specify or modify the default settings for a package.","pos":[3621,3743]},{"content":"These settings will be applied for all users when a package is deployed to a computer running the App-V 5.0 client.","pos":[3744,3859]},{"content":"To customize the settings for a package for a specific set of users on a computer or to make changes that will be applied to local user locations such as HKCU, the UserConfig file should be used.","pos":[3861,4056]},{"content":"To modify the default settings of a package for all users on a machine or to make changes that will be applied to global locations such as HKEY<ph id=\"ph1\">\\_</ph>LOCAL<ph id=\"ph2\">\\_</ph>MACHINE and the all users folder, the DeploymentConfig file should be used.","pos":[4057,4284]},{"content":"The UserConfig file provides configuration settings that can be applied to a single user without affecting any other users on a client:","pos":[4286,4421]},{"content":"Extensions that will be integrated into the native system per user:- shortcuts, File-Type associations, URL Protocols, AppPaths, Software Clients and COM","pos":[4427,4580]},{"content":"Virtual Subsystems:- Application Objects, Environment variables, Registry modifications, Services and Fonts","pos":[4586,4693]},{"content":"Scripts (User context only)","pos":[4699,4726]},{"content":"Managing Authority (for controlling co-existence of package with App-V 4.6)","pos":[4732,4807]},{"content":"The DeploymentConfig file provides configuration settings in two sections, one relative to the machine context and one relative to the user context providing the same capabilities listed in the UserConfig list above:","pos":[4809,5025]},{"content":"All UserConfig settings above","pos":[5031,5060]},{"content":"Extensions that can only be applied globally for all users","pos":[5066,5124]},{"content":"Virtual Subsystems that can be configured for global machine locations e.g. registry","pos":[5130,5214]},{"content":"Product Source URL","pos":[5220,5238]},{"content":"Scripts (Machine context only)","pos":[5244,5274]},{"content":"Controls to Terminate Child Processes","pos":[5280,5317]},{"content":"File structure","pos":[5323,5337]},{"content":"The structure of the App-V 5.0 Dynamic Configuration file is explained in the following section.","pos":[5339,5435]},{"content":"Dynamic User Configuration file","pos":[5441,5472]},{"pos":[5474,5549],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Header<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> - the header of a dynamic user configuration file is as follows:"},{"pos":[5555,5757],"content":"?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"utf-8\"?<ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;gt;&amp;lt;</ph>UserConfiguration <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>PackageId<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>=\"1f8488bf-2257-46b4-b27f-09c9dbaae707\" DisplayName=\"Reserved\" xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/appv/2010/userconfiguration\""},{"pos":[5763,5830],"content":"The <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>PackageId<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> is the same value as exists in the Manifest file."},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Body<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> - the body of the Dynamic User Configuration file can include all the app extension points that are defined in the Manifest file, as well as information to configure virtual applications.","pos":[5832,6028]},{"content":"There are four subsections allowed in the body:","pos":[6029,6076]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Applications<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> - All app-extensions that are contained in the Manifest file within a package are assigned with an Application ID, which is also defined in the manifest file.","pos":[6082,6257]},{"content":"This allows you to enable or disable all the ex